<dl id="n26277d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n26" href="#n26277d">N26 (VI.B.18)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n26all.htm#n26277d"> 277(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> the loth word <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n26277d"><li>FW 300.11 </li><li><a href="../../flex/lg/lexlg.htm#n26277d">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/lg/l39lg.htm#n26277d">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n26277d">MS BL 47478-10</ms> </li><li>JJA 53:064 <a name="lgd4" href="../../FF/fdra/lda.htm#lgd4">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/lg/lgd4.htm#n26277d">Draft: II.2&sect;8.4</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;Dear brother,&rdquo; said Bleoberis to Blamor, &ldquo;remember of what kin you are, and how Sir Launcelot is our cousin, and suffer death rather than shame, for none of our blood was yet shamed in battle.&rdquo; &ldquo;Fear not,&rdquo; answered Sir Blamor stoutly, &ldquo;that I will ever disgrace our kin. Yonder knight is a goodly man, but I will never yield, nor say <mark>the loth word</mark>. He may smite me down by his chivalry, but he shall slay me before I say the loth word.&rdquo; <small> Mabel Quiller-Couch, <a name="TRIS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#TRIS"><cite title="source">Cornwall's Wonderland</cite></a> (1914) 215</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
